{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875255122,"sessionID":"ses_2859af2f6ffe6Dgxn0a1FnVUa2","part":{"id":"prt_d7a69dcd7001JUSnFtYBDTK6W9","messageID":"msg_d7a699b62001bWrVQKzgq9EKZ2","sessionID":"ses_2859af2f6ffe6Dgxn0a1FnVUa2","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_functions.bash:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"wc -l /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md && head -50 /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md","description":"Check the delta-spec.md file"},"output":"1067 /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md\n# AR-016: PicoD 文件管理 API (File Management API) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-016  \n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md)\n\nThe PicoD File Management API provides a high-level interface for file operations within sandbox environments. It supports reading, writing, listing, deleting files, and managing directory structures with security constraints including path traversal prevention, file size limits, and access control.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: FileManager Interface\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `FileManager` interface that supports file read, write, delete, list operations, and directory management within sandbox environments.\n\n#### Scenario: ReadFile returns file contents\n- **GIVEN** a valid `FileManager` instance\n- **AND** a sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-abc123\"` exists\n- **AND** file `/workspace/data.txt` exists in the sandbox with content \"hello world\"\n- **WHEN** `ReadFile(ctx, \"sess-abc123\", \"/workspace/data.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL resolve the sandbox by SessionID\n- **AND** fetch the file contents from the sandbox\n- **AND** return a `FileContent` with `Data=[]byte(\"hello world\")`\n- **AND** return `nil` error on success\n\n#### Scenario: ReadFile returns error for non-existent file\n- **GIVEN** a valid `FileManager` instance\n- **AND** a sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-abc123\"` exists\n- **AND** file `/workspace/missing.txt` does NOT exist\n- **WHEN** `ReadFile(ctx, \"sess-abc123\", \"/workspace/missing.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrFileNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: ReadFile enforces path traversal protection\n- **GIVEN** a valid `FileManager` instance\n- **AND** a sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-abc123\"` exists\n- **AND** a request with path `../../../etc/passwd`\n- **WHEN** `ReadFile(ctx, \"sess-abc123\", \"../../../etc/passwd\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL reject the path\n- **AND** return `ErrInvalidPath: path traversal not allowed`\n- **AND** SHALL NOT query the sandbox\n\n#### Scenario: WriteFile creates new file\n- **GIVEN** a valid `FileManager` instance\n- **AND** a sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-abc123\"` exists\n- **AND** file `/workspace/newfile.txt` does NOT exist\n","metadata":{"output":"1067 /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md\n# AR-016: PicoD 文件管理 API (File Management API) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-016  \n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md)\n\nThe PicoD File Management API provides a high-level interface for file operations within sandbox environments. It supports reading, writing, listing, deleting files, and managing directory structures with security constraints including path traversal prevention, file size limits, and access control.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: FileManager Interface\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `FileManager` interface that supports file read, write, delete, list operations, and directory management within sandbox environments.\n\n#### Scenario: ReadFile returns file contents\n- **GIVEN** a valid `FileManager` instance\n- **AND** a sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-abc123\"` exists\n- **AND** file `/workspace/data.txt` exists in the sandbox with content \"hello world\"\n- **WHEN** `ReadFile(ctx, \"sess-abc123\", \"/workspace/data.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL resolve the sandbox by SessionID\n- **AND** fetch the file contents from the sandbox\n- **AND** return a `FileContent` with `Data=[]byte(\"hello world\")`\n- **AND** return `nil` error on success\n\n#### Scenario: ReadFile returns error for non-existent file\n- **GIVEN** a valid `FileManager` instance\n- **AND** a sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-abc123\"` exists\n- **AND** file `/workspace/missing.txt` does NOT exist\n- **WHEN** `ReadFile(ctx, \"sess-abc123\", \"/workspace/missing.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrFileNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: ReadFile enforces path traversal protection\n- **GIVEN** a valid `FileManager` instance\n- **AND** a sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-abc123\"` exists\n- **AND** a request with path `../../../etc/passwd`\n- **WHEN** `ReadFile(ctx, \"sess-abc123\", \"../../../etc/passwd\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL reject the path\n- **AND** return `ErrInvalidPath: path traversal not allowed`\n- **AND** SHALL NOT query the sandbox\n\n#### Scenario: WriteFile creates new file\n- **GIVEN** a valid `FileManager` instance\n- **AND** a sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-abc123\"` exists\n- **AND** file `/workspace/newfile.txt` does NOT exist\n","exit":0,"description":"Check the delta-spec.md file","truncated":false},"title":"Check the delta-spec.md file","time":{"start":1775875255101,"end":1775875255119}}}}
